 816:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** /*******************************************************************************
 817:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** * Function Name: CapSense_CheckBaselineDuplication
 818:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** ****************************************************************************//**
 819:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *
 820:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** * \brief
 821:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  Checks that the baseline of the specified widget/sensor is not corrupted by
 822:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  comparing it with a baseline inverse copy.
 823:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *
 824:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** * \details
 825:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  This function validates the integrity of baseline of sensor by comparing
 826:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  the conformity of the baseline and its inversion.
 827:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *
 828:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  If the baseline does not match its inverse copy:
 829:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  1. The widget ID is stored to the CapSense_INV_BSLN_WDGT_ID_VALUE register
 830:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  2. The sensor ID is stored to the CapSense_INV_BSLN_SNS_ID_VALUE register
 831:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  3. The CapSense_TST_BSLN_DUPLICATION bit is set in the
 832:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *     CapSense_TEST_RESULT_MASK_VALUE register.
 833:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *
 834:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  The function never clears the CapSense_TST_BSLN_DUPLICATION bit.
 835:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  If the CapSense_TST_BSLN_DUPLICATION bit is set, the CapSense_INV_BSLN_WDGT_ID_VALUE
 836:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  and CapSense_INV_BSLN_SNS_ID_VALUE registers are not updated.
 837:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *
 838:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  It is possible to execute a test for all the widgets using CapSense_RunSelfTest() function
 839:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  with the CapSense_TST_BSLN_DUPLICATION mask.
 840:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  In this case, the CapSense_INV_BSLN_WDGT_ID_VALUE and
 841:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  CapSense_INV_BSLN_SNS_ID_VALUE registers contain the widget and
 842:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  sensor ID of the first detected fail.
 843:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *
 844:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  The function updates the wdgtWorking register CapSense_WDGT_WORKING<Number>_VALUE
 845:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  by clearing the widget-corresponding bit. Those non-working widgets are skipped by
 846:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  the high-level API. Restoring a widget to its working state should be done by the application le
 847:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *
ARM GAS  C:\Users\ash750\AppData\Local\Temp\cchIVX1d.s 			page 18


 848:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  The test is integrated into the CapSense Component. All CapSense
 849:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  processing functions like CapSense_ProcessAllWidgets()
 850:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  or CapSense_UpdateSensorBaseline() automatically verify the baseline
 851:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  value before using it and update its inverse copy after processing.
 852:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  If fail is detected during a baseline update a CYRET_BAD_DATA result
 853:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  is returned. The baseline initialization functions do not verify the
 854:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  baseline and update the baseline inverse copy.
 855:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *
 856:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** * \param widgetId
 857:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  Specifies the ID number of the widget to be processed.
 858:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  A macro for the widget ID can be found in the
 859:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  CapSense Configuration header file defined as
 860:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  CapSense_<WidgetName>_WDGT_ID.
 861:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *
 862:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** * \param sensorId
 863:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  Specifies the ID number of the sensor within the widget.
 864:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c **** *  A macro for the sensor ID within the specified widget can be found in
