1084:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         * \brief
1085:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  Checks the specified widget/sensor for shorts to GND, VDD or other sensors.
1086:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *
1087:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         * \details
1088:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  This function performs several tests to verify a specified sensor that
1089:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  is not electrically shorted and in good condition to reliably detect
1090:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  user interactions.
1091:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *
1092:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  This function performs tests to check if the specified sensor is shorted to:
1093:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * GND, VDD
1094:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * Other GPIOs used by CapSense (such as sensors, Tx, Rx,
1095:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     shield electrodes, and external capacitors)
1096:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * Other non-CapSense GPIOs (only if they are configured
1097:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     in a strong high or low state during the test execution).
1098:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *
1099:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  The absolute resistance of an electrical short must be less than 1500 Ohm
1100:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  including all series resistors on the sensor for the short to be detected
1101:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  to GND, VDD or GPIOs. For example, if a series resistor on a sensor is
1102:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  560 Ohm (as recommended) and the sensor is shorted with another sensor,
1103:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  the function can detect a short of 380 Ohm or less as there are two
1104:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  560 ohm resistors between the shorted sensor GPIOs.
1105:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *
1106:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  The function executes the following flow to detect a short:
1107:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * Configures all the Component controlled GPIOs to strong-drive-low,
1108:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     and the specified sensor GPIO to resistive Pull up mode.
1109:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * A delay of CapSense_SNS_SHORT_TIME_VALUE in microseconds.
1110:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * Checks the status of the specified sensor for the expected state
1111:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     (logic high).
1112:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * Configures all CapSense controlled GPIOs to strong-drive-high,
1113:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     and the specified sensor GPIO to resistive Pull down mode.
1114:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * A delay of CapSense_SNS_SHORT_TIME_VALUE in microseconds.
1115:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * Checks the status of the specified sensor for the expected state
1116:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     (logic low).
1117:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * The test result is stored in CapSense Data Structure.
1118:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     A short is reported only when the sensor status check returns
1119:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     an unexpected state.
1120:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *
1121:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  Due to the sensor parasitic capacitance and internal pull-up/down resistor,
1122:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  logic high-to-low (and vice versa) transitions require setting time before
1123:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  checking the sensor status. A 2-us delay is used as the setting time and can
1124:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  that be changed using the CapSense_SNS_SHORT_TIME_VALUE parameter.
1125:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *
1126:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *  This function updates the following statuses if a short is detected:
1127:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * The widget ID is stored to the
1128:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     CapSense_SHORTED_WDGT_ID_VALUE register.
1129:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * The sensor ID is stored to the CapSense_SHORTED_SNS_ID_VALUE
1130:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     register.
1131:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * The CapSense_TST_SNS_SHORT bit is set in the
1132:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     CapSense_TEST_RESULT_MASK_VALUE register.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\ash750\AppData\Local\Temp\cchIVX1d.s 			page 23


1133:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * If CapSense_TST_SNS_SHORT is already set due to a previously
1134:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     detected fault on any of the sensor, this function does not update
1135:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     the CapSense_SHORTED_WDGT_ID_VALUE and
1136:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     CapSense_SHORTED_SNS_ID_VALUE registers. For this reason,
1137:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     clear CapSense_TST_SNS_SHORT prior to calling this function.
1138:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * The widget is disabled by clearing the correcting bit
1139:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     (CapSense_WDGT_WORKING<Number>_VALUE) in the wdgtWorking
1140:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     register. The widget is ignored by a high-level function during
1141:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     further scans and data processing tasks. The application layer can
1142:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     be set to the corresponding bit to restore the widget operation.
1143:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * To check all the Component sensor at once, use the
1144:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     CapSense_RunSelfTest() function with the
1145:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     CapSense_TST_SNS_SHORT mask.
1146:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *   * To detect an electrical short or fault condition with resistance
1147:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     higher than 1500 ohm, the CapSense_GetSensorCapacitance()
1148:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****         *     function can be used as the fault condition changes the
