2713:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     /******************************************************************************
2714:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     * Function Name: CapSense_GetSensorCapacitance
2715:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     ****************************************************************************//*
2716:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2717:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     * \brief
2718:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  Measures the specified widget/sensor capacitance.
2719:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2720:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     * \details
2721:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  This function measures the capacitance of the specified sensor
2722:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  element in femtofarads.
2723:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2724:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  For a CSX sensor, measurement is done on either Rx or Tx electrodes.
2725:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  For a CSD sensor, measurement is done on a sensor (refer to the
2726:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  sensorElement description). If the specified sensor element is
2727:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  a ganged one, the capacitance is measured for all the electrodes
2728:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  that belong to the sensor.
2729:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2730:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  For the latest measurement, the result is stored in the
2731:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  CapSense_RAM_SNS_CP_STRUCT data structure and
2732:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  the CapSense_<WidgetName>_PTR2SNS_CP_VALUE register
2733:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  is the pointer to the array with the measured
2734:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  capacitance of all sensors in the widget.
2735:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2736:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  In addition to the measuring sensor capacitance, this function
ARM GAS  C:\Users\ash750\AppData\Local\Temp\cchIVX1d.s 			page 57


2737:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  is used to identify various fault conditions with sensors such
2738:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  as electrically opened sensors. For example, the PCB track is broken
2739:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  or shorted to other nodes in the system - in all of these conditions,
2740:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  the sensor capacitance is changed which can be compared
2741:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  against pre determined capacitance for the sensor to detect a
2742:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  fault condition.
2743:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2744:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  This function must not be called if the Component is in
2745:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  the busy state.
2746:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2747:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  Capacitance is measured independently of sensor scan configuration.
2748:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  To measure sensor capacitance, the CSD sensing method is used and
2749:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  the capacitance is calculated as follows:
2750:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2751:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  Cs = R * IGain * ICode / ((2^Res - 1) * Vref * SnsClk)
2752:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2753:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  where (default value):
2754:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  * Cs - the sensor capacitance.
2755:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  * R - the measured raw count value.
2756:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  * IGain - idac gain
2757:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  * ICode - idac code (Compensation IDAC is disabled).
2758:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  * Res - the scanning resolution.
2759:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  * Vref - the reference voltage.
2760:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  * SnsClk - the sensor clock frequency.
2761:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2762:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  The measurement is performed differently for the 3rd and 4th generation
2763:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  CSD HW blocks.
2764:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2765:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  * 3rd generation CSD HW block:
2766:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    The function performs a successive approximation search algorithm
2767:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    to find appropriate IDAC code for the sensor in the specified widget
2768:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    that provides a raw count to the target of the 85% level
2769:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    of the raw count maximum value.
2770:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    Then Cs is calculated. If the raw count is within +/- 10% of the
2771:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    desired target the function returns through measurementStatusPtr
2772:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    CapSense_TST_MEASUREMENT_SUCCESS, otherwise
2773:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    CapSense_TST_MEASUREMENT_LOW_LIMIT or
2774:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    CapSense_TST_MEASUREMENT_HIGH_LIMIT is returned.
2775:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    The measured Cp range for the 3rd generation CSD HW block is from 5 pF
2776:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    to 65 pF.
2777:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    The default meaurement parameter values are:
2778:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    * IGain = 1.2 uA
2779:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    * Res = 12 bits
2780:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    * Vref = 1.2 V
2781:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    * SnsClk = 1.5 MHz
2782:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2783:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  * 4th generation CSD HW block:
2784:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    The function performs up to 4 scans
2785:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    to reach the raw count in a range between 7.5% and 45% of the maximum
2786:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    value (2^Res - 1).
2787:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    If a raw count is less than 7.5% of the maximum limit (2^Res - 1), the
2788:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    function returns CapSense_TST_LOW_LIMIT through the
2789:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    measurementStatus pointer.
2790:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    If a raw count is between 7.5% and 45% of the maximum, the function
2791:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    calculates the sensor capacitance, updates the register map and
2792:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    returns CapSense_TST_SUCCESS. If a raw count is above 45% of
2793:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    the maximum, the function measures again with a 4x increased
ARM GAS  C:\Users\ash750\AppData\Local\Temp\cchIVX1d.s 			page 58


2794:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    current (I), and repeats the measurement until the raw count is
2795:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    within 7.5% to 45% of the maximum value or gets 4x bigger.
2796:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    The minimum measurable input by this function for the 4th generation
2797:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    CSD HW block is 1pF and the
2798:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    maximum is 384pF limited by the RC time constant
2799:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    (Cs < 1 / (2*5*SnsClk*R), where R is the total sensor series
2800:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    resistance which includes on-chip GPIO resistance ~500 Ohm and
2801:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    external series resistance).
2802:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    The default meaurement parameter values are:
2803:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    * IGain = 1.2 uA
2804:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    * Res = 12 bits
2805:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    * Vref = 1.2 V
2806:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *    * SnsClk = 375 kHz
2807:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2808:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  The measurement accuracy for both generation is about 15%.
2809:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2810:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  By default, sensors that are not being measured are configured to
2811:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  strong-drive-low during the measurement. This state can be changed to
2812:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  High-Z or Shield using the CapSense_SetInactiveElectrodeState()
2813:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  function. CSD and CSX sensors have independent parameters to configure
2814:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  inactive electrode states.
2815:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2816:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  A Cmod capacitor is required for the measurement. If a dedicated Cmod
2817:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  is not available (e.g. the design has CSX widgets only), CintA and CintB
2818:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  capacitors are combined by the Component to form Cmod.
2819:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2820:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  The sensor measurement is done on all the sensors using
2821:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  the CapSense_RunSelfTest() function along with
2822:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  the CapSense_TST_SNS_CAP mask. The measurement operation
2823:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  requires reconfiguration of the hardware, hence measurement of
2824:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  all sensors together is recommended to avoid hardware reconfiguration
2825:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  for optimized firmware execution.
2826:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2827:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     * \param widgetId
2828:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  Specifies the ID number of the widget to be processed.
2829:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  A macro for the widget ID is in the CapSense Configuration
2830:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  header file defined as CapSense_<WidgetName>_WDGT_ID.
2831:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2832:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     * \param sensorElement
2833:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  Specifies the ID of the sensor element within the widget to be measured.
2834:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2835:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  For the CSD widgets, sensorElement is the sensor ID and is in
2836:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  the CapSense Configuration header file defined as:
2837:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  * CapSense_<WidgetName>_SNS<SensorNumber>_ID.
2838:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2839:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  For the CSX widgets, sensorElement is defined either as Rx ID or Tx ID.
2840:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  The first Rx in a widget corresponds to sensorElement = 0, the
2841:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  second Rx in a widget corresponds to sensorElement = 1, and so on.
2842:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  The last Tx in a widget corresponds to
2843:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  sensorElement = (RxNum + TxNum - 1). Macros for Rx and Tx IDs can
2844:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  be found in the CapSense Configuration header file defined as:
2845:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  * CapSense_<WidgetName>_RX<RXNumber>_ID
2846:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  * CapSense_<WidgetName>_TX<TXNumber>_ID.
2847:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
2848:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     * \param measurementStatusPtr
2849:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  Specifies the pointer to the CapSense_TST_MEASUREMENT_STATUS_ENUM
2850:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  variable where the result of the function execution is stored:
ARM GAS  C:\Users\ash750\AppData\Local\Temp\cchIVX1d.s 			page 59


2851:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  - CapSense_TST_MEASUREMENT_SUCCESS - The measurement completes
2852:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                        successfully, the result is valid.
2853:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  - CapSense_TST_MEASUREMENT_BAD_PARAM - The input parameter is invalid.
2854:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  - CapSense_TST_MEASUREMENT_LOW_LIMIT - The measured capacitance is below
2855:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                         the minimum possible value.
2856:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                         The measurement result is invalid.
2857:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                         It is possible that the sensor was
