3210:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     * Function Name: CapSense_GetShieldCapacitance
3211:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     ****************************************************************************//*
3212:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
3213:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     * \brief
3214:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  Measures the shield electrode capacitance.
3215:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
3216:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     * \details
3217:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  This function measures the capacitance of the shield electrode and
3218:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  returns a result. If the shield consists of several electrodes, the
3219:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  total capacitance of all shield electrodes is reported. The measured
3220:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  capacitance is stored in the CapSense_SHIELD_CAP_VALUE register
3221:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  of the data structure.
3222:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
3223:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  This function uses an algorithm identical to the sensor capacitance
3224:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  measurement (for more detail, refer
3225:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  to CapSense_GetSensorCapacitance()).
3226:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
3227:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  In addition to measuring the shield capacitance, this function is used to
3228:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  identify various fault conditions with a shield electrode such as an
3229:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  electrically open shield electrode, e.g. the PCB track is broken or
3230:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  shorted to other nodes in the system – in all of these conditions,
3231:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  this function returns elevated capacitance that can be compared
3232:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  against pre-determined capacitance for the shield electrode to
3233:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  detect a fault condition.
3234:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
3235:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  By default, all sensors are configured to Strong-drive-low mode
3236:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  while measuring the shield capacitance. This state can be changed to
3237:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  High-Z or Shield using the CapSense_SetInactiveElectrodeState()
3238:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  function and repeat the measurement.
3239:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
3240:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  This test can be executed using the CapSense_RunSelfTest()
3241:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  function with the CapSense_TST_SH_CAP mask.
3242:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
3243:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     * \param measurementStatusPtr
3244:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  Specifies the pointer to the CapSense_TST_MEASUREMENT_STATUS_ENUM
3245:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  variable where the result of the function execution is stored:
3246:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  - CapSense_TST_MEASUREMENT_SUCCESS - The measurement completes
3247:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                       successfully, the result is valid.
3248:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  - CapSense_TST_MEASUREMENT_BAD_PARAM - The input parameter is invalid.
3249:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  - CapSense_TST_MEASUREMENT_LOW_LIMIT - The measured capacitance is below
ARM GAS  C:\Users\ash750\AppData\Local\Temp\cchIVX1d.s 			page 66


3250:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                         the minimum possible value.
3251:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                         The measurement result is invalid.
3252:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                         It is possible that the sensor was
3253:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                         shorted to VDD or a sensor PCB track
3254:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                         was broken (open sensor).
3255:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  - CapSense_TST_MEASUREMENT_HIGH_LIMIT - The measured capacitance is above th
3256:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                          maximum possible value.
3257:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                          The measurement result is invalid.
3258:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                          It is possible that the sensor was
3259:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                          shorted to GND.
3260:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  - CapSense_TST_MEASUREMENT_ERROR - an unexpected fault occurred during
3261:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                     the measurement, the measurement may need
3262:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *                                     to be repeated.
3263:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *
3264:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     * \return
3265:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  Returns the capacitance of a shield in femtofarads. The status of
3266:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  measurement is returned through the measurementStatus pointer.
3267:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  If measurementStatus is not CapSense_TST_MEASUREMENT_SUCCESS, the returned
3268:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  value should be ignored. For more details, refer to the measurementStatus
3269:Generated_Source\PSoC4/CapSense_SelfTest.c ****                     *  description.
